<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="492" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1526,2021]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,320,1526,1552]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Type Material</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[334,441,1526,1552]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">
<typeStatus box="[334,441,1526,1552]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Syntypes</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
: The Perty Collection (housed at 
<collectionCode box="[815,893,1526,1552]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/a6ms-py1z" name="Zoologische Staatssammlung" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">ZSMC</collectionCode>
) includes two pairs (male and female on a single pin) of specimens that were identified as 
<typeStatus box="[633,731,1563,1589]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Perty" authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[775,1048,1562,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis box="[775,979,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Penthetria nigrita</emphasis>
Perty
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Reiss, F. &amp; Schacht, W." box="[1096,1375,1562,1588]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" pagination="307 - 312" refId="ref35940" refString="Reiss, F. &amp; Schacht, W. (1983) Die Typen der von J. B. v. Spix und C. F. Ph. v. Martius gesammelten und von M. Perty beschriebenen Dipterenarten (Insecta) in der Zoologischen Staatssammlung Munchen. Spixiana Supplement, 9, 307 - 312." type="journal article" year="1983">Reiss &amp; Schacht (1983)</bibRefCitation>
; several additional, apparently conspecific, specimens without labels are also present in the collection (Dieter Doczkal (
<collectionCode box="[159,239,1634,1660]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/a6ms-py1z" name="Zoologische Staatssammlung" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">ZSMC</collectionCode>
) pers. comm. 2019). Through the kindness of Marion Kotrba (
<collectionCode box="[967,1049,1634,1660]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/a6ms-py1z" name="Zoologische Staatssammlung" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">ZSMC</collectionCode>
), photographs of the two pairs of 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,1671,1697]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">syntypes</typeStatus>
were provided, including a photograph of one of the labels (“1. / 
<collectingCountry box="[976,1046,1670,1696]" name="Brazil" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Brasil</collectingCountry>
. / P. / 
<taxonomicName authority="Pty." authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[1110,1238,1670,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">nigrita Pty.</taxonomicName>
”). While the label does not explicitly identify it has a type, it does identify it as 
<taxonomicName authority="Perty" authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[847,1019,1707,1733]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis box="[847,951,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">P. nigrita</emphasis>
Perty
</taxonomicName>
as well as indicate that it came from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,222,1742,1768]" name="Brazil" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, which is the type locality given by Perty (1830); concurring with 
<bibRefCitation author="Reiss, F. &amp; Schacht, W." box="[972,1242,1742,1768]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" pagination="307 - 312" refId="ref35940" refString="Reiss, F. &amp; Schacht, W. (1983) Die Typen der von J. B. v. Spix und C. F. Ph. v. Martius gesammelten und von M. Perty beschriebenen Dipterenarten (Insecta) in der Zoologischen Staatssammlung Munchen. Spixiana Supplement, 9, 307 - 312." type="journal article" year="1983">Reiss &amp; Schacht (1983)</bibRefCitation>
, these specimens are here treated as the 
<typeStatus box="[402,500,1779,1805]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Perty." authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[538,811,1778,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis box="[538,739,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Penthetria nigrita</emphasis>
Perty.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="493" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1526,2021]" lastBlockId="42.[151,1436,150,214]" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="493" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1814,1840]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hardy, D. E." box="[325,479,1814,1841]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" pagination="367 - 547" refId="ref33819" refString="Hardy, D. E. (1945) Revision of Nearctic Bibionidae, including Neotropical Plecia and Penthetria (Diptera). Kansas University Science Bulletin, 30, 367 - 547." type="journal article" year="1945">Hardy (1945)</bibRefCitation>
noted: “The description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[803,879,1815,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis box="[803,879,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">nigrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is insufficient to positively identify the species, however, if Perty actually had a 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[519,637,1850,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[519,637,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Penthetria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
before him there can be little doubt but that it was the common South American species.” However, based on the aforementioned photographs (habitus, wing, head, antennae, mouthparts, and male terminalia) of the 
<typeStatus box="[462,560,1923,1949]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Perty" authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[598,866,1922,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis box="[598,799,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Penthetria nigrita</emphasis>
Perty
</taxonomicName>
, it is clear that the specimens that Perty had before him were, in fact, not 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[398,516,1958,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[398,516,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Penthetria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but are conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="Wiedemann. As" authorityName="Wiedemann. As" box="[805,1161,1958,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagiata">
<emphasis box="[805,976,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Plecia plagiata</emphasis>
Wiedemann. As
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[1168,1271,1959,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis box="[1168,1271,1959,1984]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">P. nigrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described in 1830 and 
<taxonomicName box="[291,412,1994,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagiata">
<emphasis box="[291,412,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">P. plagiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described in 1824, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[684,760,1995,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis box="[684,760,1995,2020]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">nigrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is transferred to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pinto &amp; Amorim" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[950,1022,1994,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[950,1022,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Plecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and becomes a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="493" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagiata">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="493" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">P. plagiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Considering this, the Neotropical 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[642,760,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[642,760,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Penthetria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species previously treated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hardy, D. E." box="[1103,1255,150,177]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" pagination="367 - 547" refId="ref33819" refString="Hardy, D. E. (1945) Revision of Nearctic Bibionidae, including Neotropical Plecia and Penthetria (Diptera). Kansas University Science Bulletin, 30, 367 - 547." type="journal article" year="1945">Hardy (1945)</bibRefCitation>
and subsequent authors as 
<taxonomicName authority="Perty" authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[271,538,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis box="[271,472,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Penthetria nigrita</emphasis>
Perty
</taxonomicName>
is described under the new name 
<taxonomicName authority="Fitzgerald" authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2021" box="[919,1282,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neonigrita">
<emphasis box="[919,1161,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Penthetria neonigrita</emphasis>
Fitzgerald
</taxonomicName>
(see above).
</paragraph>
